Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle, gradual curve. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium red-brown; many small inclusions.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 14? 2011,5003.288 is an alternative candidate for the identification. Remains of ink show that this was first registered as 1925,0119.469.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1619)
